# Backend Configuration
#
# The dev server picks its backend in this order (see frontend/vite.config.ts):
#
# 1. VITE_BACKEND_URL — an explicit override, always wins. Point it at a specific
#    instance subdomain, or a local backend. Leave empty to fall through.
# 2. VITE_APEX_DOMAIN — a deployment's stable apex. The game backend lives on a
#    rotating instance subdomain ({slug}.{apex}), never the apex (which is the
#    static landing), so the dev server discovers the current slug at startup from
#    https://{apex}/instances.json. You normally don't set this by hand: the
#    `BACKEND=game|edu|ethz` selector loads the matching frontend/.env.{deployment}
#    (which sets VITE_APEX_DOMAIN), so `BACKEND=game bun run dev:app` points the dev
#    server at the live game deployment — no slug is ever hardcoded.
# 3. Neither set — the local backend on http://localhost:8000 (plain `bun run dev:app`).
VITE_BACKEND_URL=

# Examples:
# VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://mar-27-2026.energetica-game.org   # a specific live instance
# VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000                     # local backend
# VITE_APEX_DOMAIN=energetica-game.org                       # discover the live instance
#
# VITE_LOBBY_URL — overrides where the app bundle's "log in" bounce points in local
# dev when no apex is set (default http://localhost:5174, the lobby dev server).
# VITE_APP_URL — the mirror: overrides where the lobby bundle's "enter run" links
# point in local dev when no apex is set (default http://localhost:5173, the app
# dev server). Both make the full local stack (`bun run dev`) clickable end to end.
